The paper discusses the use of probabilistic models of human behavior in robotics, specifically in the context of robot inference and prediction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for decision-making that takes into account continuous trajectory spaces, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also includes a user study, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the new model for robot learning, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
